### Filing a DMCA Notice
To submit a DMCA notice, please provide the following information:

1. Description of the Copyrighted Work: Identify the copyrighted work that you believe has been infringed.
   
2. Description of the Infringing Material: Specify the material that you claim is infringing and that you wish to have removed or disabled, including its location (e.g., URL or other identifying details).

3. Contact Information: Provide your address, telephone number, and email address so that we can reach you if necessary.

4. Good Faith Statement: Include the following statement:
   *"I have a good faith belief that the use of the copyrighted material I am complaining of is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law (e.g., as a fair use)."*

5. Accuracy and Authority Statement: Include the following statement:
   *"The information in this notice is accurate and, under penalty of perjury, I am the owner, or authorized to act on behalf of the owner, of the copyright or of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed."*

6. Signature: Provide an electronic or physical signature of the copyright owner or an authorized representative.

